 of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705207,"age":42,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705208,"age":44,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705212,"age":77,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705213,"age":99,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mary was born in 1543, in England. She married William Dennis in 1560, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1543–":"1543–Surnud","1540–1575":"1540–1575","1564–1614":"1564–1614","1543–Female":"1543–Surnud","1560":"1560","1558":"1558","1543":"1543","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1564":"1564","1575":"1575","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1549":"1549","1614":"1614","Stoke, Warwickshire, England":"Stoke, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1543–":"1543–Kuollut","1540–1575":"1540–1575","1564–1614":"1564–1614","1543–Female":"1543–Kuollut","1560":"1560","1558":"1558","1543":"1543","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1564":"1564","1575":"1575","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1549":"1549","1614":"1614","Stoke, Warwickshire, England":"Stoke, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"1543–":"1543–Décédée","1540–1575":"1540–1575","1564–1614":"1564–1614","1543–Female":"1543–Décédée","1560":"1560","1558":"1558","1543":"1543","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1564":"1564","1575":"1575","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1549":"1549","1614":"1614","Stoke, Warwickshire, England":"Stoke, Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mary est née en 1543, à Angleterre. Elle a épousé William Dennis en 1560, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1543–":"1543–Verstorben","1540–1575":"1540–1575","1564–1614":"1564–1614","1543–Female":"1543–Verstorben","1560":"1560","1558":"1558","1543":"1543","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1564":"1564","1575":"1575","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1549":"1549","1614":"1614","Stoke, Warwickshire, England":"Stoke, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England